  "prompt": "How do people write poems on Instagram font typewriter?",
  "response": "Writing poems on Instagram using a font that resembles a typewriter can be achieved through several methods. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide:\n\n### Method 1: Using Online Font Generators\n1. **Choose a Font Generator**: Visit a website that offers Instagram font generators, such as:\n   - [LingoJam](https://lingojam.com/InstagramFonts)\n   - [Cool Symbol](https://coolsymbol.com/cool-fancy-text-generator.html)\n   - [Font Generator (Fonts for Instagram)](https://www.fontgeneratoronline.com/)\n\n2. **Select the Typewriter Font**: Look for a font that resembles a typewriter. Common options include:\n   - `\ud835\ude72\ud835\ude98\ud835\ude9e\ud835\ude9b\ud835\ude92\ud835\ude8e\ud835\ude9b \ud835\ude7d\ud835\ude8e\ud835\udea0`\n   - `\ud835\ude7c\ud835\ude98\ud835\ude97\ud835\ude98\ud835\ude9c\ud835\ude99\ud835\ude8a\ud835\ude8c\ud835\ude8e\ud835\ude8d`\n\n3. **Type Your Poem**: Enter your poem into the text box on the font generator website.\n\n4. **Copy the Output**: The generator will convert your text into the selected font. Copy the styled text.\n\n5. **Paste on Instagram**: Open Instagram and paste the styled text into your caption, bio, or post.\n\n### Method 2: Using Mobile Apps\n1. **Download a Font App**: There are several apps available that allow you to generate and use different fonts on Instagram. Examples include:\n   - Stylish Text (Android)\n   - Fancy Key (iOS)\n\n2. **Choose the Typewriter Font**: Open the app and select a typewriter-like font (e.g., Courier New or Monospace).\n\n3. **Type Your Poem**: Enter your poem in the app and it will be automatically styled.\n\n4. **Copy and Paste**: Copy the styled text and paste it into Instagram.\n\n### Method 3: Using ASCII Art\n1. **Find an ASCII Typewriter Font**: ASCII art can mimic the look of a typewriter. You can find pre-made ASCII fonts or create your own.\n\n2. **Create Your Poem**: Write your poem in the ASCII typewriter font.\n\n3. **Post on Instagram**: Copy and paste the ASCII text into your Instagram post or caption.\n\n### Tips:\n- **Formatting**: Instagram\u2019s text formatting is limited, so test how your poem looks in the app before posting.\n- **Hashtags**: Use relevant hashtags like #TypewriterPoetry or #InstaPoetry to reach a broader audience.\n- **Visuals**: Pair your poem with a typewriter-themed image or background to enhance the aesthetic.\n\nBy using these methods, you can effectively share your poems on Instagram with a typewriter font, adding a unique and vintage touch to your posts.",
